{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 12:07:01.207167", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\nSummary of submitted solution:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"host_2_1_1_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_static_blackhole\"]\n\nExplanation (brief):\n- Diagnosis indicates host_2_1_1_1 had a PERMANENT/static neighbor (ARP) entry mapping the gateway IP to an incorrect MAC, causing local L2/L3 reachability failures. This behavior matches a host-side static blackhole of traffic to the gateway (host_static_blackhole). I identified host_2_1_1_1 as the faulty device and submitted the root cause accordingly.\n\nIf you want, I can now provide recommended remediation steps and verification commands to clear the static neighbor on the host, confirm connectivity, and rule out secondary causes (iptables, port flapping).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2600, "output_tokens": 171, "total_tokens": 2771, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
